🚀 Node.js Deployment on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu + PM2 + Nginx)

This guide explains how to deploy a Node.js + Express application on an AWS EC2 Ubuntu server using traditional Linux server setup practices.

🖥️ Prerequisites
AWS EC2 instance (Ubuntu)
SSH access (.pem file)
Basic Linux knowledge
Git repository (optional)
📦 1. Connect to EC2 Server
ssh -i "EC2.pem" ubuntu@<your-ec2-public-ip>
📦 2. Update System
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
🟢 3. Install Node.js & npm

Install Node.js on Ubuntu server:

sudo apt install nodejs npm -y
Check versions:
node -v
npm -v
📁 4. Setup Project Directory
mkdir Devops
cd Devops
If using Git:
git clone <repo-url>
cd <project-folder>
📦 5. Install Dependencies

Inside your project folder:

npm install
⚙️ 6. Create Express Server

Create a file:

nano server.js
Add this code:
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
    res.send("Server running on EC2");
});

app.listen(3000, "0.0.0.0", () => {
    console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
🚀 7. Install PM2 (Process Manager)

PM2

sudo npm install -g pm2
Start application:
pm2 start server.js
Monitor:
pm2 list
pm2 logs
🔥 8. Install Nginx

Nginx

sudo apt install nginx -y
Check status:
systemctl status nginx
⚙️ 9. Configure Nginx Reverse Proxy

Edit configuration:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
Replace location / block:
location / {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:3000;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
}
Test config:
sudo nginx -t
Restart Nginx:
sudo systemctl restart nginx
🌐 10. AWS Security Group Setup

AWS Security Groups

Open these ports:

Type	Port	Source
SSH	22	Your IP
HTTP	80	0.0.0.0/0
Custom TCP	3000	0.0.0.0/0 (optional)
🌍 11. Access Application
Direct Node.js access:
http://<your-ec2-ip>:3000
Nginx (Recommended):
http://<your-ec2-ip>
🔁 12. Restart Services
pm2 restart all
sudo systemctl restart nginx
📊 13. Monitoring Commands
pm2 logs
pm2 list
sudo ss -tulpn | grep 3000
📁 14. Basic Linux Commands
pwd                 # current directory
ls                  # list files
ls -la              # detailed list
cd /                # root directory
cd ~                # home directory
cd folder_name      # enter folder
mkdir folder_name   # create folder
rmdir folder_name   # remove folder
rm file.txt         # delete file
rm -rf folder       # force delete folder
clear               # clear terminal
📄 15. File Operations
touch file.txt      # create file
nano file.txt       # edit file
cat file.txt        # view file
cp file1 file2      # copy file
mv file1 file2      # move/rename file
🧠 Architecture Flow
Browser → Nginx (Port 80) → Node.js (Port 3000) → PM2 Process Manager
⚠️ Common Issues
1. Site not opening
Check AWS Security Group ports (80 / 3000)
2. Nginx error
sudo nginx -t
3. Node not running
pm2 list
🏁 Final Result

A production-ready deployment using traditional server architecture:

✔ Ubuntu
✔ Node.js
✔ PM2
✔ Nginx
✔ Amazon Web Services